==English==

===Alternative spellings===
'''kotow'''

===Etymology===
Cantonese Chinese [[叩頭]] / [[叩头]] (kau3 tau4), ''kau3'' knock + ''tau4'' head

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aʊ|-aʊ]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{intransitive}} To [[kneel]] and [[bow]] low enough to touch one's [[forehead]] to the ground.
# {{intransitive}} To [[bow]] very deeply.
# {{figurative}} To act in a very [[submissive]] manner.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of kowtowing.

